{\par \b Syntax:}\par excircle(Point1, Point2, Point3)\par
{\par \b Description:}\par excircle(A,B,C) draws the A-excircle of the ABC triangle.  \par \par Draws one of the excircles of a triangle, a circle tangent to one side of the triangle and also tangent to the extensions of the other two sides.\par
{\par \b Example:}\par excircle(GA, GB, GC) draws the circle tangent to BC and to the rays AB and AC.\par }